cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL

This paper is about variations of recurrent neural networks with gated units, which are commonly used in natural language processing and computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the models on image data (MNIST) and text data (Reuters Newswire Topics), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces new model variants that simplify the design and reduce the number of parameters, which could be of interest to researchers in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
